  "doc_id": "38221",
  "text": "Nutrition is one of the lifestyle factors, especially there is evidence that cancer cases have been increasing in people where the rate of obesity and nutritional disorders is high [CITATION_1] . It is agreed that the risk of many cancers can be reduced by improved dietary behaviors. Various studies have shown that eating a sufficient amount of fruits and vegetables have a preventive impact on cancer development. The most consistent findings showed that focus on diet rich in fruits and vegetables probably reduced the risk for cancers of the oral cavity, esophagus, stomach and colorectal (9). Salim et al. showed that the low incidence of colorectal cancer in the Arabian countries is due to the high intake of fruits and vegetables [CITATION_2] . There is possibly an unfavorable association between high intake of red meat and risk of cancer. Preserved meat and red meat are related to increasing the risk of colorectal cancer [CITATION_3] . It is possible that intake of deep fried food is one of the potential causes of breast cancer [CITATION_4] .",
